    • Method Detail

      • getDisplayName

        java.lang.String getDisplayName()
        Returns the display name of the configuration type. This is used, for example, to represent the configuration type in the run configurations tree, and also as the name of the action used to create the configuration.
        Returns:
        the display name of the configuration type.

      • getConfigurationTypeDescription

        java.lang.String getConfigurationTypeDescription()
        Returns the description of the configuration type. You may return the same text as the display name of the configuration type.
        Returns:
        the description of the configuration type.

      • getIcon

        javax.swing.Icon getIcon()
        Returns the 16x16 icon used to represent the configuration type.
        Returns:
        the icon

      • getId

        java.lang.String getId()
        The ID of the configuration type. Should be camel-cased without dashes, underscores, spaces and quotation marks. The ID is used to store run configuration settings in a project or workspace file and must not change between plugin versions.

      • getTag

        default java.lang.String getTag()
        The name of the run configuration group in a configuration file. The same rules as for id. Useful when id cannot be changed.

      • getConfigurationFactories

        ConfigurationFactory[] getConfigurationFactories()
        Returns the configuration factories used by this configuration type. Normally each configuration type provides just a single factory. You can return multiple factories if your configurations can be created in multiple variants (for example, local and remote for an application server).
        Returns:
        the run configuration factories.

      • getHelpTopic

        default java.lang.String getHelpTopic()
        Returns the topic in the help file or in Web Help which is shown when help for configurations of this type is requested.
        Returns:
        the help topic, or null if no help is available

      • isManaged

        default boolean isManaged()
        Is configuration fully managed by RunManager.
